HEADWORD: Entomophthoraceae
<hw>Entomophthoraceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a natural family of mostly
parasitic lower fungi that typically develop in the bodies of
insects.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Entomophthoraceae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
